    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> but failing to attest once or twice is not a big deal usually\r\n\r\nI understand, but in our case all my validators connected to Erigon failed to attest once or twice, furthermore just after the merge.\r\n\r\n> additionally the client syncing should not impact attestations in sepolia's case unless someone committed a new validator exactly at that time\r\n\r\nAfter a quick talk with Ben Eddington (Teku), we conclude to that:\r\n\r\n1. EL (Erigon) is out of sync right after the merge, which implies that\r\n2. All calls from BN (Teku) to EL (Erigon) returns 503 (service not available), which imples that\r\n3. No attestations are done since we may attest to an invalid block\r\n\r\nThe root cause of missing attestations seems to be \"Erigon is out of sync\".\r\n\r\n==> Do we have an explanation why Erigon was out of sync right after the merge?\r\n(I just try to understand what happened)",
